modules.name: AWS.ServiceCatalog
modules.comments:
AWS Service Catalog

AWS Service Catalog enables organizations to create and manage catalogs of IT services that are approved for use on AWS. To get the most out of this documentation, you should be familiar with the terminology discussed in AWS Service Catalog Concepts.

declarations.comments: Accepts an offer to share the specified portfolio.
declarations.title: acceptPortfolioShare

declarations.comments: Associates the specified principal ARN with the specified portfolio.
declarations.title: associatePrincipalWithPortfolio

declarations.comments: Associates the specified product with the specified portfolio.
declarations.title: associateProductWithPortfolio

declarations.comments: Associate the specified TagOption with the specified portfolio or product.
declarations.title: associateTagOptionWithResource

declarations.comments:
Copies the specified source product to the specified target product or a new product.

You can copy a product to the same account or another account. You can copy a product to the same region or another region.

This operation is performed asynchronously. To track the progress of the operation, use DescribeCopyProductStatus.
declarations.title: copyProduct

declarations.comments: Creates a constraint.
declarations.title: createConstraint

declarations.comments: Creates a portfolio.
declarations.title: createPortfolio

declarations.comments: Shares the specified portfolio with the specified account.
declarations.title: createPortfolioShare

declarations.comments: Creates a product.
declarations.title: createProduct

declarations.comments:
Creates a plan. A plan includes the list of resources to be created (when provisioning a new product) or modified (when updating a provisioned product) when the plan is executed.

You can create one plan per provisioned product. To create a plan for an existing provisioned product, the product status must be AVAILBLE or TAINTED.

To view the resource changes in the change set, use DescribeProvisionedProductPlan. To create or modify the provisioned product, use ExecuteProvisionedProductPlan.
declarations.title: createProvisionedProductPlan

declarations.comments:
Creates a provisioning artifact (also known as a version) for the specified product.

You cannot create a provisioning artifact for a product that was shared with you.
declarations.title: createProvisioningArtifact

declarations.comments: Creates a TagOption.
declarations.title: createTagOption

declarations.comments: Deletes the specified constraint.
declarations.title: deleteConstraint

declarations.comments:
Deletes the specified portfolio.

You cannot delete a portfolio if it was shared with you or if it has associated products, users, constraints, or shared accounts.
declarations.title: deletePortfolio

declarations.comments: Stops sharing the specified portfolio with the specified account.
declarations.title: deletePortfolioShare

declarations.comments:
Deletes the specified product.

You cannot delete a product if it was shared with you or is associated with a portfolio.
declarations.title: deleteProduct

declarations.comments: Deletes the specified plan.
declarations.title: deleteProvisionedProductPlan

declarations.comments:
Deletes the specified provisioning artifact (also known as a version) for the specified product.

You cannot delete a provisioning artifact associated with a product that was shared with you. You cannot delete the last provisioning artifact for a product, because a product must have at least one provisioning artifact.
declarations.title: deleteProvisioningArtifact

declarations.comments:
Deletes the specified TagOption.

You cannot delete a TagOption if it is associated with a product or portfolio.
declarations.title: deleteTagOption

declarations.comments: Gets information about the specified constraint.
declarations.title: describeConstraint

declarations.comments: Gets the status of the specified copy product operation.
declarations.title: describeCopyProductStatus

declarations.comments: Gets information about the specified portfolio.
declarations.title: describePortfolio

declarations.comments: Gets information about the specified product.
declarations.title: describeProduct

declarations.comments: Gets information about the specified product. This operation is run with administrator access.
declarations.title: describeProductAsAdmin

declarations.comments: Gets information about the specified product.
declarations.title: describeProductView

declarations.comments: Gets information about the specified provisioned product.
declarations.title: describeProvisionedProduct

declarations.comments: Gets information about the resource changes for the specified plan.
declarations.title: describeProvisionedProductPlan

declarations.comments: Gets information about the specified provisioning artifact (also known as a version) for the specified product.
declarations.title: describeProvisioningArtifact

declarations.comments:
Gets information about the configuration required to provision the specified product using the specified provisioning artifact.

If the output contains a TagOption key with an empty list of values, there is a TagOption conflict for that key. The end user cannot take action to fix the conflict, and launch is not blocked. In subsequent calls to ProvisionProduct, do not include conflicted TagOption keys as tags, or this causes the error "Parameter validation failed: Missing required parameter in Tags[N]:Value". Tag the provisioned product with the value sc-tagoption-conflict-portfolioId-productId.
declarations.title: describeProvisioningParameters

declarations.comments:
Gets information about the specified request operation.

Use this operation after calling a request operation (for example, ProvisionProduct, TerminateProvisionedProduct, or UpdateProvisionedProduct).
declarations.title: describeRecord

declarations.comments: Gets information about the specified TagOption.
declarations.title: describeTagOption

declarations.comments: Disassociates a previously associated principal ARN from a specified portfolio.
declarations.title: disassociatePrincipalFromPortfolio

declarations.comments: Disassociates the specified product from the specified portfolio.
declarations.title: disassociateProductFromPortfolio

declarations.comments: Disassociates the specified TagOption from the specified resource.
declarations.title: disassociateTagOptionFromResource

declarations.comments: Provisions or modifies a product based on the resource changes for the specified plan.
declarations.title: executeProvisionedProductPlan

declarations.comments: Lists all portfolios for which sharing was accepted by this account.
declarations.title: listAcceptedPortfolioShares

declarations.comments: Lists the constraints for the specified portfolio and product.
declarations.title: listConstraintsForPortfolio

declarations.comments: Lists the paths to the specified product. A path is how the user has access to a specified product, and is necessary when provisioning a product. A path also determines the constraints put on the product.
declarations.title: listLaunchPaths

declarations.comments: Lists the account IDs that have access to the specified portfolio.
declarations.title: listPortfolioAccess

declarations.comments: Lists all portfolios in the catalog.
declarations.title: listPortfolios

declarations.comments: Lists all portfolios that the specified product is associated with.
declarations.title: listPortfoliosForProduct

declarations.comments: Lists all principal ARNs associated with the specified portfolio.
declarations.title: listPrincipalsForPortfolio

declarations.comments: Lists the plans for the specified provisioned product or all plans to which the user has access.
declarations.title: listProvisionedProductPlans

declarations.comments: Lists all provisioning artifacts (also known as versions) for the specified product.
declarations.title: listProvisioningArtifacts

declarations.comments: Lists the specified requests or all performed requests.
declarations.title: listRecordHistory

declarations.comments: Lists the resources associated with the specified TagOption.
declarations.title: listResourcesForTagOption

declarations.comments: Lists the specified TagOptions or all TagOptions.
declarations.title: listTagOptions

declarations.comments:
Provisions the specified product.

A provisioned product is a resourced instance of a product. For example, provisioning a product based on a CloudFormation template launches a CloudFormation stack and its underlying resources. You can check the status of this request using DescribeRecord.

If the request contains a tag key with an empty list of values, there is a tag conflict for that key. Do not include conflicted keys as tags, or this causes the error "Parameter validation failed: Missing required parameter in Tags[N]:Value".
declarations.title: provisionProduct

declarations.comments: Rejects an offer to share the specified portfolio.
declarations.title: rejectPortfolioShare

declarations.comments:
Lists the provisioned products that are available (not terminated).

To use additional filtering, see SearchProvisionedProducts.
declarations.title: scanProvisionedProducts

declarations.comments: Gets information about the products to which the caller has access.
declarations.title: searchProducts

declarations.comments: Gets information about the products for the specified portfolio or all products.
declarations.title: searchProductsAsAdmin

declarations.comments: Gets information about the provisioned products that meet the specified criteria.
declarations.title: searchProvisionedProducts

declarations.comments:
Terminates the specified provisioned product.

This operation does not delete any records associated with the provisioned product.

You can check the status of this request using DescribeRecord.
declarations.title: terminateProvisionedProduct

declarations.comments: Updates the specified constraint.
declarations.title: updateConstraint

declarations.comments:
Updates the specified portfolio.

You cannot update a product that was shared with you.
declarations.title: updatePortfolio

declarations.comments: Updates the specified product.
declarations.title: updateProduct

declarations.comments:
Requests updates to the configuration of the specified provisioned product.

If there are tags associated with the object, they cannot be updated or added. Depending on the specific updates requested, this operation can update with no interruption, with some interruption, or replace the provisioned product entirely.

You can check the status of this request using DescribeRecord.
declarations.title: updateProvisionedProduct

declarations.comments:
Updates the specified provisioning artifact (also known as a version) for the specified product.

You cannot update a provisioning artifact for a product that was shared with you.
declarations.title: updateProvisioningArtifact

declarations.comments: Updates the specified TagOption.
declarations.title: updateTagOption
